message.content:
A Calochortus venustus, also known as the mariposa lily, is a flowering species of plant native to California.
It typically features bright pink or lavender petals with a yellow center and fuzzy green foliage.
The petals have a velvety texture and the overall shape of the flower resembles a cup or a bowl.
The plant grows from a bulb and can reach up to 2 feet in height.
Calochortus venustus is commonly found in meadows, grasslands, and oak woodlands.
It typically blooms in the spring and the flowers can last for several weeks.
Due to their striking appearance, Calochortus venustus are often used in ornamental gardening and landscaping.
